\pard\f0\fs28   Plants from Scotland with slightly wider leaves densely tomentose on both surfaces, at least when young, have been called var.{\i  hyperborea} (D. Don) DC. They usually grow with typical plants and their status requires investigation. Similar plants occur elsewhere, particularly in the Alps.
